time<-read.csv2("time.csv",stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
time$DATE<-as.Date(time$DATE,format="%Y-%m-%d") # bez tego lepiej czytalo daty w sqldf
signal<-read.csv2("signal.csv",stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
library(sqldf)
pelneDane<-sqldf(
  'select
  tim.DATE,
  sig.Y
  from
  signal sig
  join time tim on (sig.ID=tim.ID)
  ')
plot(pelneDane,type="l")

Zwizualizowaem wg roku i miesicy. Do badania typowo miesicznego suy monthplot z pakietu ts.

time$DATE<-as.character(time$DATE) 
zagregowaneDane<-sqldf(
  'select
  strftime(\'%Y\',DATE(tim.DATE)) as ROK,
  strftime(\'%m\',DATE(tim.DATE)) as NR_MIESIACA,
  min(sig.Y) as MIN,
  max(sig.Y) as MAX,
  avg(sig.Y) as MEAN
  from
  signal sig
  join time tim on (sig.ID=tim.ID)
  group by 
  strftime(\'%Y\',DATE(tim.DATE)),
  strftime(\'%m\',DATE(tim.DATE))
  order by 1,2
  ')
range<-range(min(zagregowaneDane$MIN),max(zagregowaneDane$MAX))
plot(zagregowaneDane$MEAN,type="l",xaxt = "n",xlab="DATE",ylab="",col=2,ylim=range)
# ktoreLab<-c(1,round(length(zagregowaneDane$MEAN)/2),length(zagregowaneDane$MEAN))
ktoreLab<-quantile(1:length(zagregowaneDane$MEAN))
axis(1,at=ktoreLab,labels=paste0(zagregowaneDane$ROK,"-",zagregowaneDane$NR_MIESIACA)[ktoreLab],las=1)
lines(zagregowaneDane$MIN,type="l",col=3,lty=1)
lines(zagregowaneDane$MAX,type="l",col=4,lty=1)
legend('topleft', c("MEAN","MIN","MAX") , 
       lty=c(1,1,1), col=c(2:4), bty='n',ncol=1)
